<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf67816a3-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7105"><num value="7105">§ 7105.</num><heading> Oaths</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">An applicant for a license or certificate of registry shall take, before the issuance of the license or certificate, an oath, without concealment or reservation, that the applicant will perform faithfully and honestly, according to the best skill and judgment of the applicant, all the duties required by law.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf67816a4-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/540">97 Stat. 540</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/111/281/tVI/s613">Pub. L. 111–281, title VI, § 613</ref>, <date date="2010-10-15">Oct. 15, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/2970">124 Stat. 2970</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
